                <div id="main-info">
                    <h2 class="info-title">THE FAIR PACT Mnemonic</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>"THE FAIR PACT" is a powerful mnemonic to help you identify and remember various types of ethical dilemmas. Click on "THE FAIR PACT" in the center to begin exploring the mind map.</p>
                        <p>This mnemonic is divided into three main parts:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>"THE"</strong> - Dilemmas related to personal integrity</li>
                            <li><strong>"FAIR"</strong> - Reminders about fairness, transparency, and respect for others</li>
                            <li><strong>"PACT"</strong> - Issues related to organizational trust and honesty</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>By remembering this mnemonic, you can more easily identify and address various ethical dilemmas.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- THE group information -->
                <div id="the-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">"THE" - Personal Integrity</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>"THE" group addresses ethical dilemmas related to personal integrity, emphasizing the importance of individual behavior and honesty.</p>
                        <p>This group contains three key types of ethical dilemmas:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>T</strong> - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Taking</span> things that aren't yours</li>
                            <li><strong>H</strong> - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Hiding</span> or divulging information</li>
                            <li><strong>E</strong> - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Engaging</span> in conflicts of interest</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Click on the letters in the mind map to get more detailed information.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- FAIR group information -->
                <div id="fair-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">"FAIR" - Fairness and Respect</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>"FAIR" reminds you of the importance of fairness, transparency, and respect for others, emphasizing ethical behavior in various contexts.</p>
                        <p>This section includes four key ethical issues:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>F</strong> - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">False</span> impressions</li>
                            <li><strong>A</strong> - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Acts</span> of personal decadence</li>
                            <li><strong>I</strong> - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Interpersonal</span> abuse</li>
                            <li><strong>R</strong> - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Rules</span> violations</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Click on the letters in the mind map to get more detailed information.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- PACT group information -->
                <div id="pact-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">"PACT" - Organizational Trust</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>"PACT" group focuses on ethical misconduct related to organizational trust and honesty, addressing the maintenance of organizational integrity and responsible behavior.</p>
                        <p>This group includes four key aspects:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>P</strong> - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Permitting</span> organizational abuse</li>
                            <li><strong>A</strong> - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Aren't</span> true</li>
                            <li><strong>C</strong> - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Condoning</span> unethical actions</li>
                            <li><strong>T</strong> - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Taking</span> unfair advantage</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Click on the letters in the mind map to get more detailed information.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- T letter information -->
                <div id="t-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">T - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Taking</span> things that aren't yours</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This includes <span class="keyword the-keyword">taking</span> or using someone else's property or resources without permission.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Taking a colleague's office supplies without telling them</li>
                            <li>Using company resources for personal matters without permission</li>
                            <li>Appropriating someone else's ideas or work</li>
                            <li>Theft or embezzlement of funds</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma involves the basic principles of respecting ownership and personal property.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- H letter information -->
                <div id="h-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">H - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Hiding</span> or divulging information</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves inappropriately <span class="keyword the-keyword">hiding</span> information that should be shared, or sharing confidential information that shouldn't be disclosed.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Concealing product defects or risks</li>
                            <li>Disclosing confidential or private information</li>
                            <li>Omitting important details in reports to cover up mistakes</li>
                            <li>Sharing internal information without authorization</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma involves balancing honesty, transparency, and confidentiality.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- E letter information -->
                <div id="e-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">E - <span class="keyword the-keyword">Engaging</span> in conflicts of interest</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This refers to <span class="keyword the-keyword">engaging</span> in situations where personal interests conflict with professional responsibilities.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Using your position to secure special treatment for family or friends</li>
                            <li>Accepting gifts or favors that might influence business decisions</li>
                            <li>Doing business with relatives or friends without disclosing the relationship</li>
                            <li>Allowing personal relationships to interfere with fair assessment or decision-making</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma requires recognizing potential conflicts and managing or avoiding them appropriately.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- F letter information -->
                <div id="f-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">F - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">False</span> impressions</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves giving or allowing <span class="keyword fair-keyword">false</span> impressions, misleading others or allowing them to form an incorrect understanding.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Exaggerating product features or service capabilities</li>
                            <li>Overstating qualifications or experience on a resume</li>
                            <li>Making promises to clients or stakeholders that can't be fulfilled</li>
                            <li>Failing to correct others' misunderstandings of a situation</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma emphasizes the importance of honest and transparent communication.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- A1 letter information -->
                <div id="a1-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">A - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Acts</span> of personal decadence</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves <span class="keyword fair-keyword">acts</span> that might damage personal or professional reputation.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Excessive drinking in work environments</li>
                            <li>Inappropriate behavior in professional settings</li>
                            <li>Wasting resources or extravagant spending of company funds</li>
                            <li>Engaging in non-work-related activities during work hours</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma relates to self-discipline and professional behavior standards.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- I letter information -->
                <div id="i-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">I - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Interpersonal</span> abuse</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This includes any form of <span class="keyword fair-keyword">interpersonal</span> harassment, bullying, or disrespectful behavior toward others.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Workplace harassment or bullying</li>
                            <li>Discriminatory language or behavior</li>
                            <li>Using threats or intimidation</li>
                            <li>Disrespecting others' boundaries in professional environments</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma involves respect, dignity, and maintaining a safe, inclusive environment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- R letter information -->
                <div id="r-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">R - <span class="keyword fair-keyword">Rules</span> violations</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves violating established <span class="keyword fair-keyword">rules</span>, policies, or laws.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Breaking company policies or procedures</li>
                            <li>Ignoring safety regulations</li>
                            <li>Violating laws or industry norms</li>
                            <li>Disregarding or circumventing compliance requirements</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma emphasizes the importance of following rules and regulations, even when it might cause short-term inconvenience or cost.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- P letter information -->
                <div id="p-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">P - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Permitting</span> organizational abuse</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves <span class="keyword pact-keyword">permitting</span> or tolerating unethical behavior within an organization.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Turning a blind eye to misconduct</li>
                            <li>Failing to report known violations</li>
                            <li>Tolerating unethical practices for organizational benefit</li>
                            <li>Failing to correct harmful organizational cultures or practices</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma emphasizes that everyone has a responsibility to uphold ethical standards in an organization.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- A2 letter information -->
                <div id="a2-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">A - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Aren't</span> true</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves deliberately saying things that <span class="keyword pact-keyword">aren't</span> true or making false statements.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Providing false information in reports</li>
                            <li>Lying to clients or colleagues</li>
                            <li>Falsely reporting time, expenses, or resource usage</li>
                            <li>Making promises or assertions known to be untrue</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma directly involves the basic values of honesty and truthfulness.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- C letter information -->
                <div id="c-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">C - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Condoning</span> unethical actions</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This includes accepting, supporting, or <span class="keyword pact-keyword">condoning</span> actions known to be wrong.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Remaining silent about a colleague's unethical behavior</li>
                            <li>Making excuses or rationalizations for improper actions</li>
                            <li>Participating in cover-ups of mistakes or violations</li>
                            <li>Encouraging or rewarding problematic behavior</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma reminds us that inaction is also a choice, and may enable unethical behavior.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- T2 letter information -->
                <div id="t2-info" class="hidden">
                    <h2 class="info-title">T - <span class="keyword pact-keyword">Taking</span> unfair advantage</h2>
                    <div class="info-content">
                        <p>This involves <span class="keyword pact-keyword">taking</span> advantage of unequal power or information to gain an improper advantage.</p>
                        <p>Examples:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Using inside information for personal investments</li>
                            <li>Exploiting others' vulnerabilities or ignorance</li>
                            <li>Abusing power or position for personal gain</li>
                            <li>Exploiting situations or people for improper advantage</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>This type of ethical dilemma emphasizes the importance of fair competition and respecting equal opportunity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
